WEBVTT

00:03.571 --> 00:05.573
We want matching 2200-watt
industrial jackhammers.

00:05.606 --> 00:07.875
There's more.
Get a pen out, old man.

00:07.908 --> 00:09.610
It's weird to see
Santa outside.

00:09.643 --> 00:10.778
It feels wrong,

00:10.811 --> 00:12.313
like when there's a bird
in the airport.

00:12.346 --> 00:13.747
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, I don't mind this.

00:13.781 --> 00:16.184
Watching people smoke
while they're waiting for Santa

00:16.217 --> 00:17.518
takes me back
to my childhood.

00:17.551 --> 00:18.919
Hey, guys.
Sorry I'm late.

00:18.952 --> 00:20.988
Had to look my best
for old Saint Nick.

00:21.021 --> 00:23.191
What are we working with?

00:23.224 --> 00:24.225
Well,
he's a little sweaty,

00:24.258 --> 00:25.126
but I dig
that he's legit fat.

00:25.159 --> 00:27.528
But how rosy
are those cheeks?

00:27.561 --> 00:29.630
How merry
are those dimples?

00:29.663 --> 00:32.133
Okay, I cannot support
your Santa fetish.

00:32.166 --> 00:33.701
Look, it was very
thoughtful of you all
to keep me in the mix,

00:33.734 --> 00:34.835
but I'm gonna go.

00:34.868 --> 00:35.836
No!
No! What?

00:35.869 --> 00:37.505
Yeah, it just feels weird

00:37.538 --> 00:39.173
standing in line for Santa
on Christmas Eve

00:39.207 --> 00:40.141
without a kid.

00:40.174 --> 00:41.942
Oh, you can borrow
one of mine.

00:41.975 --> 00:44.178
Douglas, Rory
is not replaceable.

00:44.212 --> 00:45.479
Now, this first Christmas
without him is gonna be hard,

00:45.513 --> 00:47.815
but I had him last year,

00:47.848 --> 00:49.383
so I have to deal with the fact
that it's Ron's turn.

00:49.417 --> 00:52.353
I'm sure Rory's
having a blast in Hawaii.
Yeah.

00:52.386 --> 00:54.555
Hey, want to be my plus-one
to Dwayne's Christmas party?

00:54.588 --> 00:57.591
It's gonna be me, Dwayne,
and that's about it.

00:57.625 --> 00:59.093
Thanks, Miggy,
but I know myself,

00:59.127 --> 01:00.594
and tonight
is about sadness.

01:00.628 --> 01:03.397
Like "trying a recipe
from a box of crackers"-
style sadness.

01:03.431 --> 01:04.565
That's sad.

01:04.598 --> 01:05.499
-I'll see y'all in the new year.
-All righty.

01:05.533 --> 01:07.168
-Bye, Poppy.
-Bye.

01:07.201 --> 01:08.802
Yo, G!
It's almost your turn!

01:08.836 --> 01:10.171
You psyched
out of your mind?

01:10.204 --> 01:12.706
I wish, but something
happened at school

01:12.740 --> 01:15.008
that sent me
into a real spiral.

01:15.042 --> 01:17.010
[ School bell rings ]
I can't believe
it's Christmas!

01:17.044 --> 01:19.079
What did
you ask Santa for?

01:19.113 --> 01:21.282
Um, I don't mean to ruin
anything for you,

01:21.315 --> 01:23.117
but if Santa was real,

01:23.151 --> 01:26.387
he would have to visit
800 houses per second.

01:26.420 --> 01:29.223
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:29.257 --> 01:31.091
I don't want her
to be right,

01:31.125 --> 01:32.693
but things
aren't adding up.

01:32.726 --> 01:34.362
Emma:
Um, heads up, Sophie.

01:34.395 --> 01:36.697
This Santa's
weirdly religious.

01:36.730 --> 01:38.432
This Mall Santa's
a formality.

01:38.466 --> 01:40.100
This Christmas
is gonna go down

01:40.134 --> 01:41.602
just like
all the others --

01:41.635 --> 01:43.904
my mom's gonna rock it,
and Dad's gonna blow it.

01:43.937 --> 01:45.839
Angie: Is that true?

01:45.873 --> 01:47.575
Yep.
Christmas is all Mia.

01:47.608 --> 01:48.842
Every year she sends Sophie

01:48.876 --> 01:50.744
this Magic Box
of awesome presents,

01:50.778 --> 01:51.945
and I usually just end up

01:51.979 --> 01:53.681
getting her
a bunch of forgettable crap.

01:53.714 --> 01:56.450
That fights everything
I know to be true about you.

01:56.484 --> 01:57.918
-Word.
-But it's the truth.

01:57.951 --> 01:59.587
I-I phone it in.

01:59.620 --> 02:01.322
Christmas presents
are overrated anyway.

02:01.355 --> 02:03.123
That's why I keep it
super chill at my house.

02:03.157 --> 02:04.958
I just get Graham
a bunch of Legos,

02:04.992 --> 02:07.328
and he writes me a story
about the two of us.

02:07.361 --> 02:09.096
Wait, you don't exchange gifts
with anybody else?

02:09.129 --> 02:10.731
Mnh-mnh.
Not even your boyfriend?

02:10.764 --> 02:11.732
Owen? No.

02:11.765 --> 02:13.667
He's not my boyfriend.
Oh.

02:13.701 --> 02:15.436
You know, we're keeping it
at a nice, slow pace.

02:15.469 --> 02:17.137
You're up, Graham.

02:17.171 --> 02:19.106
I can't face
the big guy right now.

02:19.139 --> 02:20.741
I have too many questions.

02:20.774 --> 02:22.310
Hey, I got you, G.

02:22.343 --> 02:24.512
It's Santa time, Jack!

02:24.545 --> 02:26.079
Hey, can you hold
this little dude for me?

02:26.113 --> 02:27.748
Thanks, brotha.

02:27.781 --> 02:30.218
Yo, Santa, make some room
on that lap for a big boy!

02:30.251 --> 02:31.685
Santa: No, no, no, no.

02:31.719 --> 02:33.153
-No!
-Ah!

02:33.187 --> 02:35.756
Okay, h-he is doing this
for the kids' benefit, right?

02:35.789 --> 02:37.658
He doesn't actually
believe in Santa?

02:37.691 --> 02:39.893
I don't even want to know.
He drives our kids around.

02:39.927 --> 02:42.230
**

02:42.263 --> 02:45.199
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:45.233 --> 02:47.768
**

02:47.801 --> 02:49.603
[ Knocking on door ]

02:49.637 --> 02:50.638
Ugh.

02:50.671 --> 02:52.440
Not while
I'm taping things.

02:52.473 --> 02:56.810
**

02:56.844 --> 02:58.446
Owen?

02:58.479 --> 03:00.681
Ho...Ho...

03:00.714 --> 03:02.783
Ho...
Oh, ho!

03:02.816 --> 03:04.985
You've made
the naughty list.
[ Gasps ]

03:05.018 --> 03:06.354
[ Both laugh ]

03:06.387 --> 03:08.188
I'm sorry.
Is this horrible?
No.

03:08.222 --> 03:10.491
I mean, you know,
for anybody else, maybe, but...

03:10.524 --> 03:12.693
Oh, you know Ol' Angie D
is a Santa Hound.

03:12.726 --> 03:13.961
Mm.
Mm.

03:13.994 --> 03:15.696
Ooh, I got
a package for you.

03:15.729 --> 03:18.165
Oh. Okay.

03:18.198 --> 03:20.033
We're exchanging gifts.

03:20.067 --> 03:21.001
Well, yeah, I mean,
this is cool, right?

03:21.034 --> 03:22.536
Oh, yeah. Yeah. Very cool.

03:22.570 --> 03:23.737
[ Chuckles ]

03:23.771 --> 03:26.206
But, um, you know,
I-I rush-ordered you a gift,

03:26.240 --> 03:27.975
and that's ready for pick-up,
so I'm gonna go...

03:28.008 --> 03:29.377
-Oh. [ Chuckles ]
-...get that.

03:29.410 --> 03:30.711
You don't have to go out
on Christmas Eve.

03:30.744 --> 03:32.246
No, no, no, I wanted to,

03:32.280 --> 03:34.848
but, uh, Graham's in there
sleeping, so, um...

03:34.882 --> 03:35.916
Now you're here.

03:35.949 --> 03:37.184
And if you don't mind

03:37.217 --> 03:38.085
just hanging out
for 10 minutes,

03:38.118 --> 03:39.987
I'll be right back.

03:40.020 --> 03:40.921
Feel free to duct tape up
the wreath.

03:40.954 --> 03:42.089
If you have time.

03:42.122 --> 03:44.858
**

03:44.892 --> 03:45.859
[ Door closes ]

03:45.893 --> 03:47.194
Okay, cool.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.563
Poppy?

03:51.098 --> 03:53.701
Well, I hope you're home.
You got a lot of candles going.

03:55.836 --> 03:58.372
What do you want,
Douglas?

03:58.406 --> 04:00.708
Look, I-I know exactly
what you're going through.

04:00.741 --> 04:02.576
My first Christmas alone,

04:02.610 --> 04:05.279
all I had to do was hear
two notes from Perry Como,

04:05.313 --> 04:07.047
and it was enough
to make me cry.

04:07.080 --> 04:09.583
I never did,
but the potential was there.

04:09.617 --> 04:12.119
This holiday was not designed
with single parents in mind,

04:12.152 --> 04:14.054
and that's why
I'm gonna take a nap

04:14.087 --> 04:15.689
until it's time
to go to bed.

04:15.723 --> 04:17.725
Okay, listen, can I just throw
something out real quick?

04:17.758 --> 04:20.661
The girls and I,
we have a holiday tradition,

04:20.694 --> 04:23.531
and we would be honored
if you would join us.

04:23.564 --> 04:25.699
Douglas, I'm not in the right
emotional head space

04:25.733 --> 04:26.734
for a holiday tradition.

04:26.767 --> 04:27.835
I promise you, Poppy.

04:27.868 --> 04:29.737
I know exactly
what you need right now.

04:29.770 --> 04:32.306
A Fogerty Christmas Eve
at the club

04:32.340 --> 04:34.274
will chase away your blues.

04:34.308 --> 04:37.210
[ All yelling, cheering ]

04:37.244 --> 04:39.146
**

04:39.179 --> 04:41.114
Welcome to
the North Pole Bowl --

04:41.148 --> 04:43.083
a festive gathering
of loving families

04:43.116 --> 04:44.918
kicking the dirt
out of each other.

04:44.952 --> 04:48.121
So, you people
turned Jesus' birthday

04:48.155 --> 04:50.023
into the Olympics?

04:50.057 --> 04:52.059
Yeah. Isn't it great?

04:52.092 --> 04:53.627
Okay, I'm gonna need
both of these.

04:53.661 --> 04:55.262
And, hey, stay close.

04:55.295 --> 04:58.466
Talk about
a white Christmas.

04:58.499 --> 05:01.268
Will: [ Humming ]
[ Rapid knocking
on door ]

05:01.301 --> 05:03.103
Angie!

05:03.136 --> 05:04.605
Uh, everything all right?

05:04.638 --> 05:06.574
You're looking
especially jacked.

05:06.607 --> 05:08.342
Owen just showed up
unannounced

05:08.376 --> 05:09.477
with a gift for me!

05:09.510 --> 05:10.978
So now I have to wrap up
some of your stuff

05:11.011 --> 05:13.146
so I don't look like
a total jerk who doesn't care!

05:13.180 --> 05:14.582
How much
for this jacket?

05:14.615 --> 05:16.450
Well, first of all,
that's my team jacket

05:16.484 --> 05:17.651
from when I coached
Sophie in soccer,

05:17.685 --> 05:19.152
so $1 million.

05:19.186 --> 05:20.521
And, second,
can this wait?

05:20.554 --> 05:22.222
It's Christmas Eve.

05:22.255 --> 05:24.625
I got a ton of stuff
to wrap for Sophie --
No, it can't wait.

05:24.658 --> 05:26.894
Every store out there
is a total mob scene.

05:26.927 --> 05:29.229
You, Will Cooper,

05:29.262 --> 05:31.899
are my only chance
at a Christmas miracle.

05:31.932 --> 05:33.467
So, you're asking me
for a miracle?

05:33.501 --> 05:35.168
Yes! I am!

05:35.202 --> 05:38.071
I need to Tasmanian Devil
through your personal belongings

05:38.105 --> 05:40.474
until I find the right shirt,
gadget, or tchotchke

05:40.508 --> 05:43.677
that will save
my relationship.

05:43.711 --> 05:45.178
Only thing that's off limits
is printer ink.

05:45.212 --> 05:46.647
It's very expensive.

05:46.680 --> 05:47.948
That's fine.
[ Whispers ]
Let's ransack my house.

05:51.184 --> 05:52.352
**

05:52.386 --> 05:53.487
You're the only person
I know

05:53.521 --> 05:54.955
who does their wrapping
in the kitchen.

05:54.988 --> 05:56.690
I like working
with a chilled ribbon.

05:56.724 --> 05:58.191
You know, I don't have time
to unpack that,

05:58.225 --> 05:59.493
but just keep looking.

05:59.527 --> 06:01.729
Well, you're welcome to anything
except this pile.

06:01.762 --> 06:03.130
Those are my gifts
to Sophie.

06:03.163 --> 06:04.565
Wait.

06:04.598 --> 06:06.834
Crocs?

06:06.867 --> 06:09.169
Hand sanitizer, a --

06:09.202 --> 06:10.203
A Hollywood hat?

06:10.237 --> 06:11.639
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

06:11.672 --> 06:13.541
God, Sophie's right,
you do stink at this.

06:13.574 --> 06:15.175
[ Chuckles ]

06:15.208 --> 06:16.877
How are you someone
who phones it in at Christmas?

06:16.910 --> 06:17.778
You never phone it in.

06:17.811 --> 06:19.379
I phone stuff in
all the time.

06:19.413 --> 06:21.782
Sometimes I'll even lazily
abbreviate words,

06:21.815 --> 06:23.016
like it's no big D.

06:23.050 --> 06:25.385
Will,
look me in the eye...

06:25.419 --> 06:26.887
Yeah.

06:26.920 --> 06:28.422
In my eyes.
I am.

06:28.456 --> 06:29.990
And tell me

06:30.023 --> 06:33.561
that off-brand beef jerky

06:33.594 --> 06:34.662
is the best you can do...
[ Laughs ]

06:34.695 --> 06:37.498
...for your precious
daughter, Sophie,

06:37.531 --> 06:39.633
on her one Christmas morning,
comes but once --

06:39.667 --> 06:40.768
Of course it's not,
okay?!

06:40.801 --> 06:42.670
I am an excellent
gift giver!

06:42.703 --> 06:43.737
Finding someone
the perfect gift

06:43.771 --> 06:45.539
is the best and only way
to say

06:45.573 --> 06:46.707
"I get you, man.

06:46.740 --> 06:47.541
You are cherished."

06:47.575 --> 06:48.709
So --

06:48.742 --> 06:50.010
I lied! All right?

06:50.043 --> 06:52.613
The Magic Box
is not from Mia.

06:52.646 --> 06:53.714
It's from me!

06:53.747 --> 06:55.415
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:55.449 --> 06:57.518
Douglas: The trick
to surviving holidays

06:57.551 --> 07:00.053
is just distract yourself
from your own emotions.

07:00.087 --> 07:02.590
Some people like to mope
in front of a fire.

07:02.623 --> 07:05.526
I prefer to step on throats
at the North Pole Bowl.

07:05.559 --> 07:06.727
Woman: [ Grunts ]

07:06.760 --> 07:10.063
I was expecting
more of a Bing Crosby vibe...

07:10.097 --> 07:11.431
Referee: Break it up.
Maybe a decent martini?

07:11.465 --> 07:13.601
Hey, you know what?
Ease up on the martinis, okay?

07:13.634 --> 07:14.702
Because the twins and I,

07:14.735 --> 07:15.936
we need you to be sharp

07:15.969 --> 07:18.238
so I have a chance
of winning the grand prize --

07:18.271 --> 07:21.108
access to
the club's 19th hole.

07:21.141 --> 07:22.275
Please, Poppy.

07:22.309 --> 07:23.977
I've only seen it
in paintings.

07:24.011 --> 07:26.714
So, you only invited me here
because you needed a fourth?

07:26.747 --> 07:28.115
Technically, yes,

07:28.148 --> 07:29.216
but you want to know
what's better

07:29.249 --> 07:30.117
than being miserable
at home?

07:30.150 --> 07:32.352
Helping me meet
Dan Marino,

07:32.385 --> 07:33.787
one of the select few

07:33.821 --> 07:36.256
granted access
to the 19th hole.

07:36.289 --> 07:37.758
I have no idea
who that is.
I know.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.693
And it doesn't matter.

07:39.727 --> 07:41.128
But do you know what
I think does matter?

07:41.161 --> 07:42.462
That you're around people
right now.

07:42.496 --> 07:43.797
That's good,

07:43.831 --> 07:45.799
because where you
were headed earlier,
that was bad.

07:45.833 --> 07:46.767
It was not a good place.

07:46.800 --> 07:48.135
Okay, step right up,

07:48.168 --> 07:49.603
because you're next!

07:50.303 --> 07:52.305
Douglas, you signed me up
for an adult sack race,

07:52.339 --> 07:54.074
and you didn't
ask me first?

07:54.107 --> 07:56.744
-Move it, Poppy!
-Don't blow this for us!

07:56.777 --> 07:57.845
[ Whistle blows ]
Hop!

07:57.878 --> 07:59.379
My God, woman, hop!
You tricked me.

07:59.412 --> 08:01.715
I'm not gonna forget this.
That's good.

08:01.749 --> 08:02.783
Use that anger

08:02.816 --> 08:05.252
to crush
the other families.

08:05.285 --> 08:06.720
Oh, did you just
hip check me?!

08:06.754 --> 08:09.422
You wanna spend Christmas
in the hospital, huh?!

08:09.456 --> 08:11.224
Wait, so I don't get it.

08:11.258 --> 08:12.459
Why does Mia get
all the credit

08:12.492 --> 08:13.493
for the Magic Box

08:13.527 --> 08:14.795
when she has nothing
to do with it?

08:14.828 --> 08:16.496
Mia tries, okay?

08:16.530 --> 08:19.366
It's just
Sophie is growing so fast,

08:19.399 --> 08:21.635
and by the time the stuff
gets here from the Sudan,

08:21.669 --> 08:22.936
she's moved on
to something else.

08:22.970 --> 08:24.204
I guess I get that.

08:24.237 --> 08:25.906
Graham will be heavy
into Batman Legos,

08:25.939 --> 08:27.374
and then wham!

08:27.407 --> 08:28.809
The next minute
it's all about Star Wars Legos,

08:28.842 --> 08:30.744
and I'm sitting there
with a Lego Robin in my hand

08:30.778 --> 08:31.712
like a freakin' idiot.

08:31.745 --> 08:32.813
It's the worst.

08:32.846 --> 08:34.147
So I came up
with a simple system

08:34.181 --> 08:35.816
that'll save
Christmas for them.

08:35.849 --> 08:36.950
It doesn't sound simple.

08:36.984 --> 08:38.619
It sounds like
"Westworld"-level confusing.

08:38.652 --> 08:39.820
It's not, okay?

08:39.853 --> 08:41.622
Mia doesn't know this,
but I re-wrap her gifts.

08:41.655 --> 08:43.456
I slap a tag on it
that says, "From Dad."

08:43.490 --> 08:45.458
Then I take my awesome gifts,
I put them in the Magic Box.

08:45.492 --> 08:46.727
And boom,
perfect Christmas.

08:46.760 --> 08:49.296
Maybe you deserve
a perfect Christmas.

08:49.329 --> 08:52.132
Thank you,
that's very nice.

08:52.165 --> 08:54.501
But this is how we do Christmas
in my family.

08:54.534 --> 08:56.203
Mia is
the glitzy humanitarian,

08:56.236 --> 08:57.838
and I'm the guy
on the ground.

08:57.871 --> 08:59.039
Making lunches.

08:59.072 --> 09:00.340
Fighting
with the dentist.

09:00.373 --> 09:01.508
Why do you fight
with the dentist?

09:01.541 --> 09:03.476
Because
he doesn't get it.
Okay.

09:03.510 --> 09:05.212
Sexy niche
you've carved out for yourself.

09:05.245 --> 09:07.247
She's the amazing
gift giver,

09:07.280 --> 09:09.883
and you're the guy
who fights with the dentist.

09:09.917 --> 09:11.852
[ Slams counter ]
He fights with me!

09:13.153 --> 09:14.487
Whatever, man.

09:14.521 --> 09:16.023
You have a really weird
Christmas routine,

09:16.056 --> 09:17.825
and I think deep down,
you know that.

09:17.858 --> 09:19.827
Do you know
what's weird?

09:19.860 --> 09:21.929
Not getting your boyfriend
a Christmas present.

09:21.962 --> 09:23.831
I -- I told you,
he's not my boyfriend.

09:23.864 --> 09:25.132
Exactly!
And that's weird!

09:25.165 --> 09:26.233
What's it been?
Like, a year?

09:26.266 --> 09:27.200
What's wrong with him?

09:27.234 --> 09:28.669
Does he have
a weird birthmark?

09:28.702 --> 09:30.537
Does he say "catsup"
instead of "ketchup"?

09:30.570 --> 09:32.339
Does his apartment have,
like, a weird smell?

09:32.372 --> 09:33.674
Like, not like a bad smell
or a good smell,

09:33.707 --> 09:34.975
but just a very distinct smell,

09:35.008 --> 09:35.709
like, "What is that smell?"

09:35.743 --> 09:37.310
What's wrong? Does --

09:37.344 --> 09:38.345
Is he a bad dancer
or a good dancer?
No!

09:38.378 --> 09:40.380
It's not about Owen.

09:40.413 --> 09:41.248
[ Sighs ]

09:41.281 --> 09:43.383
It's about
Graham and Owen.

09:43.416 --> 09:46.253
There's a reason
I haven't introduced them.

09:46.286 --> 09:49.156
I'm raising a --
a 7-year-old,

09:49.189 --> 09:50.791
and it's really hard.

09:50.824 --> 09:54.161
And Owen
is a 30-year-old guy

09:54.194 --> 09:56.864
without a care in the world,
and...

09:56.897 --> 10:00.300
I just can't picture him
being ready for that.

10:00.333 --> 10:04.972
Or maybe
you're not ready for that.

10:06.073 --> 10:07.474
Yeah, maybe I'm not.

10:09.609 --> 10:11.278
Then what the heck
are you doing here, Angie,

10:11.311 --> 10:13.947
turning my house
upside-down?

10:13.981 --> 10:15.582
You got to go to him.

10:15.615 --> 10:17.017
You have
to figure this out.

10:17.050 --> 10:18.518
I think you're right.

10:18.551 --> 10:20.688
I have to go
break up with him.

10:20.721 --> 10:21.955
Uh, no.

10:21.989 --> 10:23.390
Not what I was saying
at all.

10:23.423 --> 10:25.225
[ Cheering ]

10:25.258 --> 10:27.695
You can do it, honey!
Come on!

10:27.728 --> 10:28.628
Yes!
Yes!

10:28.662 --> 10:30.630
[ Laughs ]
Yes!

10:30.664 --> 10:32.465
Come at me! Come at me!

10:32.499 --> 10:34.467
Oh, yeah! Oh, yeah.
Way to go, Emma or Amy.

10:34.501 --> 10:36.737
* La-la, la, la

10:36.770 --> 10:38.605
* 'Tis the season
to be jolly *
You got this.

10:38.638 --> 10:40.607
Oh, I know I do, Amy.

10:40.640 --> 10:43.476
* Fa-la-la-la-la,
la-la-la-la *
Be the tree.

10:44.311 --> 10:46.079
* Don we now
our gay apparel *
Ah!

10:46.113 --> 10:50.083
And that's how you win
Christmas, dirtbags!

10:50.117 --> 10:51.719
* Fa-la-la, la-la-la,
la-la-la *

10:51.752 --> 10:53.153
* Fa-la-la-la-la

10:53.186 --> 10:54.755
* Fa-la-la-la-la

10:54.788 --> 10:56.556
* Fa-la-la-la-la,
la-la-la-la *

10:56.589 --> 10:58.425
-Yes!
-Boom!

10:58.458 --> 11:00.828
And that's how you
carefully carry an ornament!

11:00.861 --> 11:02.595
I knew you
were our missing piece!

11:02.629 --> 11:04.331
Nobody's gonna be able
to catch us.

11:04.364 --> 11:07.200
Poppy? You missed a call
from Rory.

11:07.234 --> 11:09.770
He said he's going to a luau
with no service.

11:09.803 --> 11:11.404
He'll call you tomorrow.

11:11.438 --> 11:12.272
[ Sighs ]

11:12.305 --> 11:13.941
I missed a call
from my baby.

11:13.974 --> 11:16.176
But you were having a great time
with us, right?

11:16.209 --> 11:17.444
But I shouldn't be.
Not without him.

11:17.477 --> 11:19.479
No, no, come on.
Don't -- Don't leave.

11:19.512 --> 11:21.248
You're the only one
with enough speed

11:21.281 --> 11:22.883
to catch
the Christmas goose!

11:24.017 --> 11:25.418
Graham: Mom?

11:25.452 --> 11:29.189
This guy in shorts
says he's the real Santa.

11:29.222 --> 11:32.525
Merry Christmas,
Ms. D'Amato!

11:32.559 --> 11:34.261
**

11:34.294 --> 11:35.128
And now you've met
my son.

11:40.200 --> 11:41.368
Angie: Isn't it amazing
that we're standing here

11:41.401 --> 11:43.536
with the real Santa Claus?

11:43.570 --> 11:45.205
I don't know, Mom.

11:45.238 --> 11:47.775
This guy isn't doing a lot
to convince me.

11:47.808 --> 11:50.143
The details of his friendship
with the Easter Bunny

11:50.177 --> 11:52.212
keep changing.
Owen: [ Chuckles ]

11:52.245 --> 11:53.646
Your son's had
a lot of questions.

11:54.647 --> 11:56.483
Are you watching me
with cameras

11:56.516 --> 11:58.886
or is it more
of a psychic thing?
Uh...

11:58.919 --> 12:01.588
What did Abraham Lincoln
get for Christmas?

12:01.621 --> 12:04.124
Doesn't there have to be
some gray area

12:04.157 --> 12:05.592
between naughty and nice?

12:05.625 --> 12:07.394
Oh, boy. Um...

12:07.427 --> 12:08.896
Of all the actors
who played you,

12:08.929 --> 12:11.064
who do you think nailed it?

12:11.098 --> 12:12.699
Tim Allen?

12:12.732 --> 12:14.701
Does being alive
as long as you have

12:14.734 --> 12:16.870
ever feel like a curse?

12:16.904 --> 12:18.806
This little boy is not a fan
of yes or no answers.

12:18.839 --> 12:19.940
He wants details.

12:19.973 --> 12:22.242
I like to be painted
a picture.

12:22.275 --> 12:23.811
Angie: You know what?

12:23.844 --> 12:25.846
I think Santa should probably
be getting back to work.

12:25.879 --> 12:27.247
Every minute
he spends with us

12:27.280 --> 12:30.083
is another child's
Christmas ruined.

12:30.117 --> 12:31.051
That's right.
[ Chuckles ]
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:31.084 --> 12:32.752
My favorite
Christmas tradition,

12:32.786 --> 12:34.021
answering the door!

12:35.989 --> 12:37.590
Miggy?
What are you doing here?

12:37.624 --> 12:38.725
Without getting into it,

12:38.758 --> 12:40.293
me and Dwayne
are in a fight.

12:40.327 --> 12:41.862
Happens every time
we watch "Elf."

12:41.895 --> 12:44.064
So I was just
chilling at home with Jack

12:44.097 --> 12:45.765
when Graham called me
about Santa.

12:47.434 --> 12:49.236
Is this the guy, Graham?

12:49.269 --> 12:51.404
Looks like
the real deal to me.

12:51.438 --> 12:53.740
I'm not
fully convinced yet.

12:53.773 --> 12:56.076
Hmm.

12:56.109 --> 12:57.444
If you're
the real Santa Claus,

12:57.477 --> 12:59.779
do you remember the year
you brought me that N64?

12:59.813 --> 13:01.614
Yes?

13:01.648 --> 13:03.416
[ Gasps ]

13:03.450 --> 13:05.552
Did you hear that, Graham?
It all checks out.

13:05.585 --> 13:06.954
Yep. Yep.

13:06.987 --> 13:08.956
It all checks out.

13:08.989 --> 13:11.058
So, Santa should probably
be getting back to work,

13:11.091 --> 13:12.525
'cause who knows
how much longer

13:12.559 --> 13:13.560
our roof will support
the weight of his sleigh.

13:13.593 --> 13:15.929
-Yeah.
-Just one more question.

13:15.963 --> 13:18.398
A girl at my school says

13:18.431 --> 13:21.101
you'd have to visit
800 houses every second

13:21.134 --> 13:22.269
if you were real.

13:22.302 --> 13:23.636
How do you do that?!

13:23.670 --> 13:26.106
I-I know
the answer's magic,

13:26.139 --> 13:27.307
but I want
to go past that.

13:28.708 --> 13:31.244
Well, uh...
[ Chuckles ]

13:31.278 --> 13:34.147
Your friend is, um...

13:34.181 --> 13:36.116
Your friend is --

13:36.149 --> 13:37.517
is too worried
about the math.

13:37.550 --> 13:40.120
You see, I'm able to
bring holiday cheer

13:40.153 --> 13:41.922
to so many people
in one night

13:41.955 --> 13:43.623
because I have
a lot of help.

13:43.656 --> 13:44.757
Yeah, yeah.

13:44.791 --> 13:46.426
I-I got parents,
and friends,

13:46.459 --> 13:48.028
and mall Santas,

13:48.061 --> 13:50.263
and I inspire every one of them
to do their part.

13:50.297 --> 13:53.300
And so, together,
we're all Santa.

13:53.333 --> 13:55.936
And having so much help
frees me up

13:55.969 --> 13:57.770
to make special
one-on-one visits

13:57.804 --> 13:59.639
to good little
boys and girls

13:59.672 --> 14:01.774
that might need a little extra
Christmas magic.

14:01.808 --> 14:04.277
**

14:04.311 --> 14:05.612
Wow.

14:05.645 --> 14:07.114
Damn, dude.

14:07.147 --> 14:08.348
This is Santa!

14:09.482 --> 14:11.718
I never doubted you
for a second!

14:11.751 --> 14:12.886
It's been a pleasure,
sir.

14:14.121 --> 14:16.523
Yo, Santa. Come on.
I'll walk you out.

14:16.556 --> 14:18.091
Oh, Miggy?
[ Clears throat ]

14:18.125 --> 14:19.192
Don't you think
you should be

14:19.226 --> 14:21.328
getting
baby Jack back to bed?

14:21.361 --> 14:23.196
Right. Smart.

14:23.230 --> 14:26.199
He won't be coming to the crib
unless we're asleep.

14:26.233 --> 14:27.400
Good night.

14:27.434 --> 14:28.701
[ Exhales sharply ]

14:28.735 --> 14:29.469
[ Door closes ]

14:29.502 --> 14:31.638
**

14:31.671 --> 14:33.773
Angie? Will Cooper.

14:33.806 --> 14:36.876
I've been, uh, thinking about
this Magic Box situation,

14:36.910 --> 14:39.812
and, um...you were right.

14:39.846 --> 14:43.550
This year, Sophie is getting
the good presents from Dad.

14:43.583 --> 14:44.651
All right.

14:44.684 --> 14:45.885
Sorry for
so many messages.

14:45.919 --> 14:47.020
Your phone
kept cutting me off.

14:47.054 --> 14:48.521
Bye.

14:50.390 --> 14:51.124
Dad, can I --

14:52.392 --> 14:53.460
What's that?

14:53.493 --> 14:57.297
A glow-in-the-dark
ant farm?

14:57.330 --> 14:58.999
That's so cool!

14:59.032 --> 15:00.233
It must be from Mom!

15:00.267 --> 15:02.202
**

15:02.235 --> 15:04.837
Yeah.

15:04.871 --> 15:06.873
She nailed it again.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.376
But unfortunately,

15:09.409 --> 15:11.911
because of the 2018
Christmas Code of Conduct,

15:11.945 --> 15:13.080
since you're out of bed,

15:13.113 --> 15:14.514
I have to give this
to Toys for Tots --

15:14.547 --> 15:15.448
I was never here!

15:15.482 --> 15:17.017
Okay.

15:17.050 --> 15:18.585
**

15:18.618 --> 15:20.353
I guess we can add
"meeting sexy Santa"

15:20.387 --> 15:21.488
to the list of things

15:21.521 --> 15:23.190
that he'll eventually
tell his therapist.

15:23.223 --> 15:24.791
[ Chuckles ]

15:24.824 --> 15:26.359
Should we open
these gifts?

15:26.393 --> 15:29.862
Um...

15:29.896 --> 15:32.832
Wait, I have to tell you
something.

15:32.865 --> 15:34.934
I was ready
to end this tonight.

15:34.968 --> 15:39.772
'Cause I didn't know
if I could see you with my son.

15:39.806 --> 15:42.109
And then I watched you

15:42.142 --> 15:44.211
convince him
that Santa really exists,

15:44.244 --> 15:47.214
and...you're wonderful.

15:47.247 --> 15:48.381
[ Sighs ]

15:48.415 --> 15:50.017
I didn't get you a gift.

15:50.050 --> 15:52.252
I wish I had,

15:52.285 --> 15:54.421
because I'm sure
whatever this is

15:54.454 --> 15:55.888
is really thoughtful --

15:55.922 --> 15:57.057
I got you a candle.

15:59.292 --> 16:00.260
Vanilla?

16:00.293 --> 16:01.995
Is this the same kind

16:02.029 --> 16:04.264
we have in the bathroom
at work?
Yep.

16:04.297 --> 16:05.732
Realized that
after the fact.

16:05.765 --> 16:07.100
Real bummer.

16:07.134 --> 16:07.934
[ Laughs ]
[ Sighs ]

16:07.967 --> 16:09.369
Look,
I got all in my head

16:09.402 --> 16:11.038
about where we were
as a couple.

16:11.071 --> 16:12.172
Mm-hmm.
Are we jewelry?

16:12.205 --> 16:13.906
Are we "Owen Bucks"?

16:13.940 --> 16:15.408
I needed to get
something that showed
how much I like you

16:15.442 --> 16:17.110
while also
not spooking you.

16:17.144 --> 16:18.645
And that gift
does not exist.

16:18.678 --> 16:19.779
So, therefore, candle.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.114
Candle.
Yeah.

16:22.015 --> 16:23.983
Owen...

16:24.017 --> 16:25.652
I'm rusty at this.

16:26.819 --> 16:28.355
Will you be my boyfriend?

16:28.388 --> 16:29.722
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

16:29.756 --> 16:31.424
Okay. [ Laughs ]

16:31.458 --> 16:35.228
**

16:35.262 --> 16:35.962
Can you put the beard
back on?

16:35.995 --> 16:36.963
Oh, definitely.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.098
Okay.
Yeah.

16:38.131 --> 16:39.299
[ Chuckles ]
It's Christmas.

16:39.332 --> 16:40.167
[ Doorbell rings ]

16:40.200 --> 16:42.169
-Hey.
-Hey.

16:42.202 --> 16:44.504
-Merry Christmas.
-We cut this down ourselves.

16:44.537 --> 16:45.872
Yeah, your neighbor
can send me a bill.

16:45.905 --> 16:47.874
-Keys.
-Yep.

16:47.907 --> 16:50.110
-Where are they going?
-To get the stand.

16:50.143 --> 16:52.179
They've done this before.
[ Sighs ]

16:52.212 --> 16:54.481
Look, Douglas,
I appreciate the gesture,

16:54.514 --> 16:57.050
but you guys
don't want to be here.

16:57.084 --> 17:00.553
I put a pair of Rory's PJs
on the couch cushion...

17:00.587 --> 17:02.289
and, well,
we've been spooning.

17:02.322 --> 17:05.458
Okay, well,
I do want to be here.

17:05.492 --> 17:08.261
I'm not gonna try to talk you
out of being sad.

17:08.295 --> 17:10.330
I just wanted to,
uh, sit with you.

17:10.363 --> 17:13.100
All right.
Well, sit wherever you want.

17:13.133 --> 17:14.801
Just not on my son,
the couch cushion.

17:14.834 --> 17:16.669
Ahh.
[ Chuckles ]

17:16.703 --> 17:18.471
Sorry I cost you guys
the 19th hole.

17:18.505 --> 17:20.173
What, are you kidding?
We still won.

17:20.207 --> 17:21.474
By a lot.
Oh.

17:21.508 --> 17:24.144
You know, Christmas wasn't
always such a marathon

17:24.177 --> 17:25.845
like it is today.

17:25.878 --> 17:27.480
It's exhausting.

17:27.514 --> 17:29.048
I'm mad at every single one
of those damn songs.

17:29.082 --> 17:31.318
Except Mariah.
I love her.

17:31.351 --> 17:34.020
For Rose and I,
it was Perry Como.
Mm.

17:34.053 --> 17:35.888
Can you believe
I met a 27-year-old

17:35.922 --> 17:38.658
who loved Perry Como?

17:38.691 --> 17:40.059
And after she died,

17:40.093 --> 17:42.662
I just could never listen
to him again.

17:42.695 --> 17:46.533
Luckily, avoiding Perry Como
is extremely easy

17:46.566 --> 17:47.434
most of the year, so...

17:47.467 --> 17:49.836
Hmm.

17:49.869 --> 17:51.938
Holidays are hard.

17:51.971 --> 17:53.606
Ugh. I know.

17:58.145 --> 18:00.280
So, this is what it's like
when you're...

18:00.313 --> 18:02.615
not distracting yourself
from your feelings.

18:02.649 --> 18:04.184
Mm-hmm.

18:04.217 --> 18:06.453
Welcome
to the dark side.

18:06.486 --> 18:08.855
Thanks for being
here with me.

18:08.888 --> 18:11.358
It's kind of nice.

18:11.391 --> 18:12.325
Yeah.

18:13.460 --> 18:15.027
[ Door opens ]
What are you guys doing?

18:15.061 --> 18:16.929
Oh, no.
I was just, uh --

18:16.963 --> 18:18.665
Hmm...
Already bored.

18:18.698 --> 18:22.769
[ Hammering ]

18:22.802 --> 18:24.404
**

18:24.437 --> 18:26.773
He lifts, bro.

18:26.806 --> 18:28.741
Angie, Graham,
Emma and Amy don't believe me.

18:28.775 --> 18:31.178
Can you please tell them
that Santa is toned as hell?

18:31.211 --> 18:33.280
He's in excellent shape
for his age,

18:33.313 --> 18:35.047
and he's
a great listener.

18:35.081 --> 18:36.949
He was
just there with us.

18:36.983 --> 18:38.285
So present.

18:38.318 --> 18:39.986
My only complaint was that
he didn't hit us

18:40.019 --> 18:42.522
with a classic
"Ho, ho, ho."

18:42.555 --> 18:44.791
But meeting him was
what I wanted this year.

18:44.824 --> 18:45.892
And he knew that.

18:45.925 --> 18:46.793
Okay, at what point
should we be worried

18:46.826 --> 18:48.195
that he's --
Never.

18:48.228 --> 18:50.463
We must never
ask this question.
Okay.

18:50.497 --> 18:52.098
Hey,
I just wanted to say

18:52.131 --> 18:54.767
I'm sorry if I got in your head
about Owen last night.

18:54.801 --> 18:55.735
How'd he take it?

18:55.768 --> 18:58.205
Things are pretty good.

18:58.238 --> 19:00.106
He's my boyfriend now.

19:00.139 --> 19:02.041
Wow!
[ Laughs ] Yeah.

19:02.074 --> 19:03.510
Oh!

19:03.543 --> 19:04.711
That's -- That's great.

19:04.744 --> 19:06.145
Good for you.

19:06.179 --> 19:07.414
But, you know,
you should apologize

19:07.447 --> 19:09.015
about the five voicemails
you left me.

19:09.048 --> 19:11.551
[ Laughs ]
And you kept on
introducing yourself.

19:11.584 --> 19:13.119
I know it's you.
You might know other Wills.

19:13.152 --> 19:14.521
-I don't.
-Angie, look.

19:14.554 --> 19:15.622
It's from my mom.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.023
And it glows in the dark!

19:18.325 --> 19:21.461
Oh, wow!
That's really cool, Soph.

19:23.896 --> 19:25.565
I knew you weren't
gonna take credit

19:25.598 --> 19:27.300
for any of that good stuff.

19:27.334 --> 19:29.469
Yeah, but look
how happy she is.

19:31.271 --> 19:32.605
That's my perfect Christmas.

19:32.639 --> 19:35.275
Mm. I get it.

19:35.308 --> 19:38.077
There is one gift
I will take credit for.

19:39.479 --> 19:41.648
Angie,
Merry Christmas from me.

19:41.681 --> 19:42.949
Oh!

19:42.982 --> 19:52.225
**

19:52.259 --> 19:53.760
[ Chuckles ]

19:53.793 --> 19:59.232
This is, like, every story
Graham's ever written me.

20:02.001 --> 20:04.203
"'The Complete Short Stories'
by Graham D'Amato,

20:04.237 --> 20:06.273
edited by William Cooper."

20:06.306 --> 20:07.640
[ Chuckles ]

20:07.674 --> 20:09.809
You weren't shy about
taking credit on this one.

20:09.842 --> 20:11.311
Yeah, I had to get in there.

20:11.344 --> 20:12.679
Your kid loves a tangent.

20:14.213 --> 20:15.315
You get me, man.

20:15.348 --> 20:16.816
[ Chuckles ]

20:16.849 --> 20:18.017
I feel cherished.

20:18.050 --> 20:20.152
That was the goal.

20:20.186 --> 20:21.554
Douglas: Hello?

20:21.588 --> 20:23.890
Everyone shut up.
It's Dan Marino's assistant!

20:23.923 --> 20:26.259
Yes, Megan, and to you.

20:27.660 --> 20:28.628
I see.

20:28.661 --> 20:29.962
No problem.

20:29.996 --> 20:32.098
Marino's blowing me off!

20:37.203 --> 20:39.138
**

20:39.171 --> 20:40.673
What are
we looking at here?

20:40.707 --> 20:42.409
I drew a picture
of you guys!

20:42.442 --> 20:44.911
-Uh-huh.
-So, where's our present?

20:44.944 --> 20:45.878
[ Cellphone rings ]
You guys, it's Rory!

20:45.912 --> 20:47.079
It's Rory! Get together!

20:47.113 --> 20:48.214
-Ooh!
-Ooh!

20:48.247 --> 20:49.882
-Mele Kalikimaka, Rory!
-Hey, Rory!

20:49.916 --> 20:51.618
I miss you guys,

20:51.651 --> 20:53.853
and I really,
really miss you, Mom.

20:53.886 --> 20:55.388
Oh, baby. I love you.

20:55.422 --> 20:57.890
I didn't know
I could miss you so much.

20:57.924 --> 21:00.860
Mom, I know we're
having a moment,

21:00.893 --> 21:03.162
but could you please hand
the phone over to Miggy?

21:03.195 --> 21:04.531
Your framing is trash.
-You know what?

21:04.564 --> 21:05.532
Yeah, it's pretty trash.
It's okay.
I have to --

21:05.565 --> 21:06.666
I got you.
Oh.

21:06.699 --> 21:08.668
* You can't beat
home sweet home *

21:08.701 --> 21:10.370
Do you want me to skip ahead?
It's on shuffle.
Oh, no, no.

21:10.403 --> 21:13.239
That's okay.
I -- I love this song.

21:13.272 --> 21:15.875
* Oh, there's no place
like home *
Hadn't heard it
in a while.

21:15.908 --> 21:19.779
* For the holidays

21:19.812 --> 21:21.514
* For the holidays

21:21.548 --> 21:24.584
* You can't beat
home sweet home *
